==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Appertinent
<hw>Ap*per"ti*nent</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Belonging;
appertaining.</def> <altsp>[Now usually written
<asp>appurtenant</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Appertinent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Appertinent
<hw>Ap*per"ti*nent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which belongs to
something else; an appurtenant.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Appete</ent>⟦br⟧
